{{Documentation subpage}} {{CS2 wrapper|base=cite wikisource}} <!-- Categories and interwikis go at the bottom of this page. --> Creates a citation for an article in the journal [[Popular Science Monthly]] with links to a scanned and transcribed version held by [[Wikisource]].
=== Usage === <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{wsPSM|Title|Volume|Date}}</syntaxhighlight> All three parameters are required.
Note: This template accepts additional optional parameters from the template {{tl|cite wikisource}}.
=== Examples === <syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{wsPSM|Sketch of Dr. John W. Dawson|8|December 1875}}</syntaxhighlight> {{wsPSM|Sketch of Dr. John W. Dawson|8|December 1875}}
<syntaxhighlight lang="wikitext">{{wsPSM | title = Sketch of George Jarvis Brush | vol = 20 | date = November 1881 | first = T. E. | last = Lounsbury | wspage = 117 | scan = Page:Popular Science Monthly Volume 20.djvu/127 }}</syntaxhighlight> {{wsPSM | title = Sketch of George Jarvis Brush | vol = 20 | date = November 1881 | first = T. E. | last = Lounsbury | wspage = 117 | scan = Page:Popular Science Monthly Volume 20.djvu/127 }}
=== See also === * {{tl|cite wikisource}} * {{tl|Cite PSM}} * {{tl|WsPSM2}}
<includeonly>{{Sandbox other|| <!-- Categories and interwikis go here: -->
[[Category:Wikisource link templates|Popular Science Monthly]] [[Category:Internal link templates]] [[Category:Wikisource link templates]] [[Category:Templates that wrap Cite wikisource]] }}</includeonly>

